enhanced_by.reason: The asIterable method wraps an Enumeration into an Iterable, which is a similar operation to converting an Enumeration to a List.
The get method retrieves an element from an Enumeration, which can be used to set up the state before converting the Enumeration to a List.
Both methods convert an iterable type (Enumeration or Iterator) to a List, making the output of toList(Iterator) a good reference for assertions.
The get method retrieves an element from an Enumeration, which can be used to verify the contents of the List created by toList.
